      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Open Questions\n\nResolved enough for now:\n- Lifecycle events now include `fragmentMaterialize`, `fragmentFocusEnter`, `fragmentFocusLeave`, and `fragmentReload`.\n- Local fragment reload restores the focused node when possible, otherwise falls back to the fragment entry/root.\n- History remains document/session-level by default.\n\nLater follow-up only:\n- whether hooks/scripts should actively consume lifecycle events yet\n- whether any additional edge cases remain around focus restoration",
